Setup Kubernetes Cluster normal way:

The configuration of the overall K8s cluster is divided into three major segments: 
1. configuring the master node, 
2. configuring two worker nodes, and possible issues. 

The below section lists the common configuration required on all three nodes and illustrates the master configuration along the steps.

Step 1: Set Hostname and Update Hosts file
# hostnamectl set-hostname k8s-cp01
# hostnamectl set-hostname k8s-w01
# hostnamectl set-hostname k8s-w02

# vi /etc/hosts
192.168.122.156  k8s-cp01.kubernetes.local server.kubernetes.local k8s-cp01 server
192.168.122.221 k8s-w01.kubernetes.local k8s-w01
192.168.122.45 k8s-w02.kubernetes.local k8s-w02 

192.168.122.156  k8s-cp01
192.168.122.221 k8s-w01
192.168.122.45 k8s-w02

Step 2: Disable Swap Space on Each Node
# swapoff -a
# sed -i '/ swap / s/^\(.*\)$/#\1/g' /etc/fstab

Step 3: Adjust SELinux and Firewall Rules for Kubernetes
# setenforce 0
# vi  /etc/selinux/config or /etc/sysconfig/selinux 
SELINUX=disabled

On the master node, allow following ports in the firewall.
# firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port={6443,2379,2380,10250,10251,10252,10257,10259,179}/tcp
# firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=4789/udp
# firewall-cmd --reload

**** Port Details *****
Port	Protocol	Component	Purpose
6443	TCP	kube-apiserver	Main Kubernetes API endpoint. Workers, kubectl, controllers, and schedulers connect here.
2379	TCP	etcd	Client port for reading/writing cluster state to etcd.
2380	TCP	etcd	Peer communication between etcd members in a multi-master cluster.
10250	TCP	kubelet	Used by the API server to communicate with kubelets on nodes.
10251	TCP	kube-scheduler (older versions)	Scheduler metrics/health endpoint. Often unused in newer Kubernetes versions.
10252	TCP	kube-controller-manager (older versions)	Controller-manager metrics/health endpoint. Often unused in newer versions.
10257	TCP	kube-controller-manager	Secure controller-manager endpoint.
10259	TCP	kube-scheduler	Secure scheduler endpoint.
179	TCP	Calico BGP	Used when Calico operates in BGP mode for route exchange. Not required for all CNIs.
4789	UDP	VXLAN	Overlay network tunnel used by Calico VXLAN, Flannel VXLAN, etc.


Kubernetes networking components need the kernel to:

Forward packets between interfaces (ip_forward=1).
Allow bridged traffic to be inspected by iptables (bridge-nf-call-* = 1).
